<div class="prelaunch">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-1"></div>
		<div class="col-md-10">
			<h1>Stop Buying Dirty Energy. Power Your Home With<br><u>100% Renewable Electricity</u></h1>
			<h2>No installation required. No changes in service. No billing changes.</h2>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-1"></div>
	</div>
		<div class='form-inline'>

			<%= form_for(@prelaunch) do |f| %>

				<div class="form-group">
	      			<%= f.text_field :email, :class => "form-control", placeholder: "Email", :autofocus =>true %>
	  			</div>

	  			<div class="form-group zip">

	  				<%= f.text_field :zip, :class => "form-control", placeholder: "Zip Code" %>
	  			</div>

				<div class="form-group">	  
 					<%= f.submit "Send Me My Options", class: "btn btn-success" %>
				</div>
			<% end %>
		</div>

</div>

<div class="what_is_greenir">
    <div class='container'>
        <div class="col-md-7">
            <h1>What Is <span style="color: #4cae4c;">Greenir</span>?</h1>
            <h4>Greenir is a marketplace for 100% renewable electricity packages for your home or apartment.<br><br>
            Whether you are a renter or home owner, if you live in a deregulated market, you have the right to choose the energy supplier that powers your home. <br><br>
            At Greenir, we believe that people who are educated on their options will switch to renewable electricity and by partnering with the best renewable electricity suppliers in the country, we hope to provide our customers with the opportunity to decrease their carbon footprints and invest in the future of renewable energy.</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5" style="margin-top: 20px;">

            <a href="/faq"><h3>Why Should I Switch?</h3></a>
            <a href="/faq"><h3>Which Package Should I Choose?</h3></a>
            <a href="/faq"><h3>Will I Save Money?</h3></a>
            <a href="/faq"><h3>Will My Billing Change?</h3></a>
            <a href="/faq"><h3>Are The Suppliers Reliable? Will My Power Go Out?</h3></a>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>
